		<div class="comment-body"><p>Problem is it doesn&#8217;t work that way, being a land lord DOES NOT equal wealthy.  </p>
<p>I know people that rent Section 8 housing, they do okay but they sure as hell ain&#8217;t rich.  These people all have a MORTGAGE against their properties.  If what you suggest were to happen they can&#8217;t pay then they loose the property to the bank and the property is foreclosed on. </p>
<p>We have to get off this us and them shit at our own level.  THERE IS NO US AND THEM on this level, the THEM is the banks, the mega corps and the top officials, everyone else is us including the guy that runs 20 rental properties.  </p>
<p>I mean sure saying &#8220;tell the wealthy land lord to suck it&#8221; sounds great until you realize it won&#8217;t do any good because he isn&#8217;t wealthy and the true wealthy are in control and they sure are not going to tell themselves to suck it.</p>
<p>From 2008-2010 we bailed out the mortgage industry and the banks made out like bandits adn people were thrown out on their asses by the millions, don&#8217;t expect that to be different the next time around.</p>
