		<div class="comment-body"><p>Just to be clear, that wasn&#8217;t an US vs THEM comment. It was a &#8220;this could cut both ways&#8221; comment. I know a lot of renters keep mortgages on rental units and I put &#8220;wealthy&#8221; in quotes to indicate that isn&#8217;t how I view them. I know too many people to have a BS bias like that. </p>
<p>I&#8217;m just predicting that something to that effect is likely enough I&#8217;d be shocked if it didn&#8217;t happen somewhere. Obviously it would create foreclosures, but so would yanking S8 funding by itself. I&#8217;m also not advocating it or suggesting it would be a good idea. </p>
<p>I guess the key takeaway is to the rentee, the income might go away one way or the other, and the asset might go away one way or the other as well.</p>
