		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-body"><p>My son in law thought we were super rich when he first met us.   Because we have land! In his eyes lots and lots of land.  With big trees and pastures a creek.  Plus we have a house and 2 cars.  The clincher we have TWO bathrooms.  Plus we don&#8217;t have more than one generation in our house sharing expenses.  Our large land 5 ac.  Our house 1800 sq feet That is not super rich by our standards.  It was for his.  </p>
<p>He came from the country side in France.  Then he lived here with a dr. and a real estate lawyer.  They lived in a Mcmansion with a tennis court and in ground pool.  He thought we had more money than they did.  Took almost a year to get it through to him that we couldn&#8217;t just fly to vegas for the weekend because we didn&#8217;t have that kind of money.  he thought we just didn&#8217;t like him.  </p>
<p>Where he comes from only the richest of the rich have land.  His sponsor  family would travel all the time at the drop of the hat.  So his thoughts on what was rich really didn&#8217;t match up to the reality.  He gets it now but it is very hard for him sometimes.</p>
</div>

